    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="71"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6363/6–1644</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Petroleum Adviser</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                        >Rayner</hi>)<note n="26" xml:id="d71fn26">Addressed to the Secretary of
                        State and the Under Secretary.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-16">June 16,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed by the British Embassy that the following telegram was sent by the
                    Prime Minister to the President yesterday.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Many thanks for your telegram of June 7 number 554. Points of principle have
                        arisen in connection with Brown’s report which it has been necessary to take
                        up in the Cabinet, and oil being so vital to our security and other reasons
                        we have referred them to a ministerial <pb facs="0130" n="118"
                            xml:id="pg_118"/> committee, but I hope that this will not mean any
                        great delay and that I will be able to let you know how the matter stands in
                        the very near future.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>The Brown referred to above is Sir William Brown who was Chairman of the British
                    Delegation which conducted the preliminary discussions with our American Expert
                    Group.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Rayner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
